<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">This is only ideally true. From the perspective of the user of a large closed LLM, this isn&#x27;t quite right because of non-associativity, experiments, unversioned changes, etc.<p>It&#x27;s best to assume that the relationship between input and output of an LLM is not deterministic, similar to something like using a Google search API.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44369860&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44366494%2344369860" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
