<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">The reverse is possible too: throwing massive compute at a problem can mask the existence of a simpler, more general solution. General-purpose methods tend to win out over time—but how can we be sure they’re truly the most general if we commit so hard to one paradigm (e.g. LLMs) that we stop exploring the underlying structure?</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44367317&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44366494%2344367317" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
