<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">The way I see this, from the explore-exploit point of view, it&#x27;s pretty rational to put the vast majority of your effort into the one action that has shown itself to bring the most reward, while spending a small amount of effort exploring other ones. Then, if and when that one action is no longer as fruitful compared to the others, you switch more effort to exploring, now having obtained significant resources from that earlier exploration, to help you explore faster.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44367991&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44366494%2344367991" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
