<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">CS is full of trivial examples of this. You can use an optimized parallel SIMD merge sort to sort a huge list of ten trillion records, or you can sort it just as fast with a bubble sort if you throw more hardware at it.<p>The real bitter lesson in AI is that we don&#x27;t really know what we&#x27;re doing. We&#x27;re hacking on models looking for architectures that train well but we don&#x27;t fully understand why they work. Because we don&#x27;t fully understand it, we can&#x27;t design anything optimal or know how good a solution can possibly get.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368757&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44366494%2344368757" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
