<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">I imagine there’s actually combinatorial power in there though. If we imagine embedding something with only 2 dimensions x and y, we can actually encode an unlimited number of concepts because we can imagine distinct separate clusters or neighborhoods spread out over a large 2d map.  It’s of course much more possible with more dimensions.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44367418&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44366494%2344367418" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
