<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">The Bitter Lesson is specifically about AI. The lesson restated is that over the long run, methods that leverage general computation (brute-force search and learning) consistently outperform systems built with extensive human-crafted knowledge. Examples: Chess, Go, speech recognition, computer vision, machine translation, and on and on.</div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44370704&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44366494%2344370704" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
